snippet.description:
NOTICE - I'm not a firebase expert. Make sure you know good security practices before putting an app into production that uses sensitive user data!

Steps in video
1. - Setup your Local using Sveltefire-template https://github.com/codediodeio/sveltefire-template
2. - Make your Firebase Project on https://firebase.google.com/
3. - Add a web app to your Firebase Project, put config in App.svelte
4. - Make a Firestore, add these rules
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    match /posts/{postId}/{document=**} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth.uid == postId;
       }
     }
   }
5. - Allow Anonymous signin and Email signin
6. - Add Email Sign-in to template https://firebase.google.com/docs/auth/web/password-auth
7. - Deploy app with $ firebase login, $ firebase init, $ firebase deploy
